 Thatcher. Bush and Mrs. Ronnie sided with Margaret.  Thatcher suddenly seemed to be just one of the gang. At international gatherings, they usually were side by side. Bush, a veteran of world politics, knew many leaders around the globe.  Thatcher, characteristically, was tougher.  Thatcher did her part, demonstrating her loyalty. She has always been an outstanding ally of the United States, he said. They were ideological soulmates and called each other Ronnie and Margaret. Among Western allies, she was alone at Ronald Reagan's side in 1986 in supporting the US bombing of Libya. 